cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.CR

This paper deals with the design parameters of opportunistic routing in ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization of transmission spectral efficiency, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper uses an approximation function, which is a mathematical tool and could be categorized under machine learning (cs.MA). The paper also deals with system parameters such as path loss exponent and noise level, which could be related to control systems (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
